Title: The Planckian Conspiracy

ParadoxComments: 13 pages, harvmac

Journal-ref: Nucl. Phys. B456 (1995) 257

It has been argued that the consistency of quantum theory with black holephysics requires nonlocality not present in ordinary effective field theory. Weexamine the extent to which such nonlocal effects show up in the perturbativeS-matrix of string theory.